records.addlTxt: Court is down on 10-05-2022.  Court rescheduled plea/sentencing hearing.  Parties notified of date. Plea/sentencing scheduled for December 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Filed: Original Transcript of Preliminary Hearing (13 pages) commencing 05-06-2022, by Danielle N. Holcomb.

Attorney Meera L Al-Henaey in court, defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin not in court, in custody.  Patrick O'Keefe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
CASE HELD OFF THE RECORD PER JUDGE.  Case in court for a status conference.  Defense requests a plea and sentencing date.  Court scheduled the matter as requested.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 5, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Meera L Al-Henaey in court, defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin not in court, in custody.  Patrick O'Keefe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
CASE HELD OFF THE RECORD PER JUDGE.  Case in court for a scheduling conference.  Defense requests a status date.  Court set the status as requested.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Status conference scheduled for July 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed:  Attorney Meera Al-Henaey

Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin in court with Attorney Darryl Everett Smith; both appear by video.  Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin in custody.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: West Allis Officer M. Lazaris. Court took judicial notice of certified documents regarding case #* that are attached to the complaint. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.   No driving without a valid license. Scram bracelet ordered to monitor defendant maintains absolute sobriety.

Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin in court with attorney Dawn Marie Rablin.  Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin in custody.  Jessica Ann Behling appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings. Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 4. DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.   
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea
  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin not in court.   No Assistant District Attorney Available appeared for the State of Wisconsin. COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Jeremiah Nathaniel Kinikin not in court.  Claire E Zyber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited.
